P.S. So what the heck is the Prize Patrol ? I knew you were going to ask and I have the answer here somewhere- ah here it is :<br>
<br>
                             <br>
                      The Prize patrol will choose 5 - 10 posts from the past or present posts on <br>
                      forum each month that we will then vote on as a group to determine a winner. This<br>
                      can be theme based - ex. top 10 hints, best humor, story, outstanding<br>
                      achievement,most informative etc. The winner will receive a prize that is donated by<br>
                      a member(s) for this purpose or from the stock in the bank. How this is organized<br>
                      and put into play will be up to the coordinator and volunteers.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uladykaldoari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadyKaldoari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/01 12:23:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Volunteers still needed</span><hr size=1> One volunteer here for you.  If you'll take a not-even-fledgling or don't know what she is to the Guild yet.  But I'll stick around as a hopeful volunteer until you can use me. <p>Kaldaori, means "she who protects"<BR>
